	<h2>Common Compliance Failures</h2>

	<h3>Top Violation Issues</h3>
	<p>Most frequent pool fence code violations found in Stockton:</p>

	<p><strong>Gate Latch Height:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Violation:</strong> Latch below 54-inch requirement</li>
		<li><strong>Why it fails:</strong> Homeowner installed standard latch at normal door height</li>
		<li><strong>Correction:</strong> Relocate latch to 54+ inches or install compliant release mechanism</li>
		<li><strong>Cost to fix:</strong> $75-200</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Non-Self-Closing Gates:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Violation:</strong> Gate without automatic closing mechanism</li>
		<li><strong>Why it fails:</strong> Spring hinges removed, broken, or never installed</li>
		<li><strong>Correction:</strong> Install spring hinges or hydraulic closer</li>
		<li><strong>Cost to fix:</strong> $45-120 per gate</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Horizontal Rails in Climbable Zone:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Violation:</strong> Horizontal boards/rails within bottom 45 inches</li>
		<li><strong>Why it fails:</strong> Standard fence design with horizontal stringers visible</li>
		<li><strong>Correction:</strong> Redesign fence or add barrier preventing access to horizontal members</li>
		<li><strong>Cost to fix:</strong> $800-2,500 depending on fence length</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Inadequate Height:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Violation:</strong> Fence under 60 inches (5 feet) tall</li>
		<li><strong>Why it fails:</strong> Measurement error, settling, or grading change</li>
		<li><strong>Correction:</strong> Add height with fence extensions or replace</li>
		<li><strong>Cost to fix:</strong> $12-25 per linear foot for height addition</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Excessive Vertical Spacing:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Violation:</strong> Gaps between pickets exceed 4-inch sphere test</li>
		<li><strong>Why it fails:</strong> Decorative fence with 6-inch or wider spacing</li>
		<li><strong>Correction:</strong> Add additional pickets to reduce spacing</li>
		<li><strong>Cost to fix:</strong> $8-18 per linear foot</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Maintenance and Ongoing Compliance</h2>

	<h3>Regular Inspection Checklist</h3>
	<p>Quarterly checks to maintain compliant pool barrier:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Gate closing test:</strong> Release gate from various positions, verify automatic closing</li>
		<li><strong>Latch function test:</strong> Confirm latch engages every time gate closes</li>
		<li><strong>Height verification:</strong> Check for settling or grade changes reducing height</li>
		<li><strong>Gap inspection:</strong> Verify no gaps exceeding 4-inch sphere test have developed</li>
		<li><strong>Structural integrity:</strong> Check for loose boards, rust, rot, or damage</li>
		<li><strong>Hardware condition:</strong> Inspect hinges, latches, closers for wear or corrosion</li>
		<li><strong>Alarm testing:</strong> If using alarms, test monthly per manufacturer instructions</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Common Repairs to Maintain Compliance</h3>
	<p>Typical maintenance issues and solutions:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Weak gate springs:</strong> Replace spring hinges every 3-5 years ($45-85/gate)</li>
		<li><strong>Warped gates:</strong> Straighten or replace before binding prevents closing ($120-400)</li>
		<li><strong>Damaged boards:</strong> Replace immediately to prevent climbing access ($8-15/board)</li>
		<li><strong>Loose posts:</strong> Re-concrete or brace before fence height compromised ($85-150/post)</li>
		<li><strong>Corroded latches:</strong> Replace with stainless steel or coated hardware ($35-75)</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Real Estate Transactions and Pool Barriers</h2>

	<h3>Disclosure Requirements</h3>
	<p>Seller obligations regarding pool fencing:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Mandatory disclosure:</strong> Must disclose pool and safety features in Transfer Disclosure Statement</li>
		<li><strong>Compliance certification:</strong> Some buyers/lenders require certification of code compliance</li>
		<li><strong>Known defects:</strong> Must disclose non-working gates, alarms, or other barrier issues</li>
		<li><strong>Liability concern:</strong> Accidents during escrow period can create seller liability</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Pre-Sale Compliance Upgrades</h3>
	<p>Bringing pool fence into compliance before listing:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Benefits:</strong> Prevents buyer concerns, eliminates negotiation issues, reduces liability</li>
		<li><strong>Typical costs:</strong> $500-2,500 for most compliance upgrades</li>
		<li><strong>ROI:</strong> Prevents deal delays, inspection failures, price reductions</li>
		<li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Keep permit and inspection records for buyer</li>
	</ul>

